docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:3:This document specifies a live visualization layer for parallel agent execution under `rhei run` and the persistent transition journal that backs it. The design extracts a reusable frontend crate (`rhei-tui`) that can be driven by any parallel `rhei` subcommand — not only `rhei run` — and preserves the current plain-stdout behavior for non-interactive use.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:9:1. **Visualize parallel agent activity.** When `rhei run --parallel N` is running in an interactive terminal, the user sees a live view of up to N agents, each with its task id, current state, elapsed time, and a short tail of its log.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:10:2. **Keep a light transition log.** Each state transition produces exactly one line in a persistent journal. Every line carries both the transition (`from → to`) and the absolute path to the detailed log for that state.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:12:4. **Be reusable.** Any future parallel `rhei` subcommand reuses the same event surface and frontend.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:18:- Remote visualization. The TUI renders to the local terminal only.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:24:1. **Execution engine** — the existing `run_agent_mode` / `run_callback_mode` logic, refactored to emit events through an `EventSink` instead of calling `println!` directly.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:26:3. **Frontend** — either a plain stdout writer (non-TTY) or a TUI renderer (TTY). Frontend selection is decided once at startup based on `stdout.is_terminal()`, with `--tui` and `--no-tui` overrides.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:29:engine ──► Tee ──┬──► JournalSink   (runtime/transitions.log, always on)
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:40:    RunStarted    { workspace: PathBuf, parallel: u8, total_tasks: usize },
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:62:`AgentOutput` is emitted for live agent subprocess traffic after the slot is assigned and before it is released. The event is line-oriented and identifies stdout vs stderr with `AgentStream`. Lines are ordered per stream; interleaving between stdout and stderr is best-effort because the two streams are read concurrently. The per-task log file remains the complete durable transcript.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:82:- **`JournalSink`** — opens `runtime/transitions.log` in append mode at construction and writes one line per `SlotAssigned` and one line per `SlotReleased`. Line format is fixed-column and tail-friendly (see below). The journal is always written, in every mode.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:94:| Default: `stdout.is_terminal()` is true            | TuiSink    |
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:100:The renderer allocates a fixed pool of N slots matching `--parallel N`. Slots are reused as tasks complete — the grid does not grow unbounded.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:110:A persistent journal pane at the bottom shows the most recent transitions regardless of mode. Layout is recomputed on terminal resize (`crossterm::event::Event::Resize`).
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:122:`runtime/transitions.log` is a UTF-8, append-only, newline-delimited text file. Each line is one event. Columns are space-separated; columns 1–3 are fixed-width, column 4 is a path, and optional trailing fields are comma-separated key=value pairs.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:132:- The transition column uses the UTF-8 arrow `→` (U+2192).
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:141:- **Panic in the execution engine** — a panic hook registered by `TuiSink` calls `ratatui::restore()` before re-raising, so the terminal is never left in raw mode.
docs/specs/rhei-run-tui.spec.md:142:- **Ctrl+C** — because the TUI runs the terminal in raw mode, Ctrl+C arrives as a key event rather than an automatic `SIGINT`. `TuiSink` restores the terminal, explicitly re-raises `SIGINT` for the process, and then exits its render loop.
