docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:879:The `timeout` field on the transition and `agent_timeout` on the state serve different roles:
docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:884:| `timeout` | Transition definition | Which transition fires when a timeout occurs (existing field, now also used by agent mode) |
docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:886:When `agent_timeout` is set on a state but no transition with `timeout` exists from that state, the agent is killed but the task remains in its current state with a warning logged.
docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:890:Timeout transitions support the same `on_leave` and `on_enter` callbacks as any other transition. This enables notification, logging, or cleanup on timeout:
docs/specs/rhei-agents.spec.md:893:transitions:
