docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:3:This document specifies a new role in the Rhei ecosystem: the **State Machine Writer**. It designs custom state machines (YAML files) tailored to a project's specification, team structure, and workflow requirements.
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:5:For the YAML schema and transition callback system see the [Transitions Specification](rhei-transitions.spec.md). For the default state machine see the [States Specification](rhei-states.spec.md).
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:9:The default `rhei` state machine covers a generic agent workflow (draft, pending, review, completed, with optional human review). Many projects need domain-specific workflows:
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:15:The state machine writer analyzes two inputs — the **project specification** and the **project teams** — and produces a state machine YAML file that encodes the project's real workflow as Rhei states and transitions.
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:28:The state machine writer extracts from the specification:
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:35:| Failure modes and recovery paths | Error/retry states and transitions |
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:36:| Automated checks | Callback-eligible transitions |
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:46:The state machine writer maps teams to workflow elements:
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:53:| Autonomous agents | Non-gating states with agent instructions |
docs/specs/rhei-state-machine-writer.spec.md:58:The state machine writer produces a single YAML file conforming to the [YAML State Machine Format](rhei-transitions.spec.md#yaml-state-machine-format-specification). The file is ready to be referenced by a Rhei plan's `**States:**` declaration.
