docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:532:This section defines the formal structure of YAML state machine configuration files. All state machines must conform to this specification.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:538:| `name` | string | Yes | Unique identifier for the state machine |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:539:| `models` | string array | No | Declared model profile identifiers available to states in this machine |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:540:| `version` | string | Yes | Semantic version of the state machine definition |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:542:| `transitions` | array | Yes | List of allowed state transitions |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:543:| `callbacks` | object | No | Platform-specific callback mappings |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:555:    final: <boolean>            # Optional: true if this is a terminal state (no outgoing transitions)
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:556:    gating: <boolean>           # Optional: true if no autonomous (agent/engine) transitions are allowed out
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:557:    visits: <integer>           # Optional: maximum number of visits permitted for this state
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:560:    all_models: [<string>]      # Optional: list of declared model profiles; run this state once per listed model
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:561:    model: <string>             # Optional: one declared model profile allowed for this state
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:576:| `final` | boolean | No | Marks this as a terminal state. Tasks in final states cannot transition further |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:577:| `gating` | boolean | No | Marks this as a gating state. When `true`, autonomous commands (`rhei next`, `rhei complete`, engine-triggered transitions) must not transition out of this state. Only explicit human-initiated transitions (`rhei transition` with `triggeredBy: 'user'`) are allowed. |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:578:| `visits` | integer | No | Maximum number of visits permitted for this state before the loop budget is exhausted |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:581:| `all_models` | string array | No | Explicit list of declared model profile identifiers; the state runs once for each listed model |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:582:| `model` | string | No | Restricts the state to one model profile declared in the machine-level `models` list |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:585:| `agent_timeout` | string | No | Maximum time an agent may work in this state (e.g., `30m`, `1h`). When exceeded, `rhei run` kills the agent and fires a timeout transition if one is declared. |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:588:| `inputs` | artifact array | No | Required file artifacts that must exist before entering or working this state |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:589:| `outputs` | artifact array | No | Required file artifacts that must exist before leaving this state |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:590:| `mcp_servers` | array | No | MCP server entries (ids or inline definitions) attached to the agent subprocess. Individual entries may be marked `optional: true`. Mutually exclusive with `gating: true` and `program:`. See [States Specification — MCP Servers and Skills](rhei-states.spec.md#mcp-servers-and-skills). |
