docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:654:This section describes the runtime semantics of the `visits` field, also
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:655:called *counted visits* in the main plan specification and the states
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:656:specification. The three terms — `visits`, *counted visits*, and *counted
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:659:`visits` is a state-level loop budget. It is used when a workflow intentionally cycles through the same state multiple times before taking a non-loop exit.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:663:- `visits` applies to every entry into that state, including the initial entry and later loop-back re-entries.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:664:- Starting in a counted state records `metadata.tasks.<id>.stateVisits.<state-name> = 1`.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:666:- The task's active `**State:**` value mirrors that count by writing `<state>-<n>` for visits greater than `1`; visit `1` stays as the bare state name.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:667:- When evaluating transitions from a counted-loop state, runtimes should expose:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:669:  - `visits`: the configured state-level loop budget
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:670:- Once `visitCount >= visits`, further loop-back transitions into that state are exhausted and the machine must take another allowed transition such as escalation, human review, or completion.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:673:- On a state that declares [`poll:`](rhei-states.spec.md#polling-states), the same `stateVisits` entry records poll attempts. Transitions from that state may use `pollAttempts` (alias for `visitCount`) and `pollMaxAttempts` (alias for `poll.max_attempts`) for clarity; both names are only defined on transitions whose `from` state declares `poll:`. A self-loop transition from a poll state is interpreted by `rhei run` as "retry after `poll.interval`" and releases the `--parallel` slot between attempts; once `pollAttempts >= pollMaxAttempts`, the engine refuses self-loops and picks the first matching non-self-loop transition instead.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:683:      transition to `agent-review-fix`. If the loop budget is exhausted,
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:684:      transition to `human-review`.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:685:    visits: 3
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:690:      Address reviewer findings only, then transition back to `agent-review`.
