docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:717:Each transition in the `transitions` array specifies an allowed state change:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:720:transitions:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:723:    description: <string>   # Required: Explanation of when/why this transition occurs
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:724:    on_leave: <callback>    # Optional: Callback invoked when leaving the source state
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:725:    on_enter: <callback>    # Optional: Callback invoked when entering the target state
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:726:    condition: <expression> # Optional: Condition that must be true for system-triggered transitions
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:727:    timeout: <duration>     # Optional: Duration after which system triggers this transition
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:728:    exit_code: <int|array|"nonzero">  # Optional: Exit-code condition for program state transitions
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:731:    max_retries: <integer>  # Optional: Maximum retry attempts for this transition
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:737:| `from` | string | Yes | Source state name, or `"*"` for wildcard (matches any non-final state) |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:739:| `description` | string | Yes | Human-readable explanation of the transition's purpose and when it occurs |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:740:| `on_leave` | string | No | Callback function identifier invoked before leaving the source state |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:741:| `on_enter` | string | No | Callback function identifier invoked after entering the target state |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:742:| `condition` | string | No | Expression evaluated for system-triggered transitions |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:743:| `timeout` | string | No | Duration (e.g., `24h`, `30m`) after which system triggers this transition |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:744:| `exit_code` | integer, integer array, or `"nonzero"` | No | Exit-code condition for transitions from program states. Only evaluated when a program exits without calling `rhei transition`. See [Program States Specification](rhei-programs.spec.md#exit-code-transitions). |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:745:| `mcp_unavailable` | boolean or string array | No | When `true`, fires when any required MCP server on the source state fails its availability check. When an array, fires only when one of the listed ids failed. Only valid on transitions from agent states. See [Tooling-Unavailable Trigger](#7-tooling-unavailable-trigger-triggeredby-system). |
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:752:State artifact contracts (see [States Specification — Artifact Contracts](rhei-states.spec.md#artifact-contracts) for the schema) are enforced around transitions:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:754:1. Before entering a target state, the runtime resolves `target.inputs` and
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:755:   rejects the transition if any required input file does not exist.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:756:2. After `on_leave` / `on_enter` callbacks complete, but before the state write
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:757:   is committed, the runtime resolves `source.outputs` and rejects the
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:758:   transition if any required output file does not exist.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:759:3. `rhei complete` is subject to the same output checks as `rhei transition`.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:763:This makes artifact production and consumption part of the state-machine
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:769:- Matches any state **except** final states (states with `final: true`)
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:770:- Specific transitions take precedence over wildcard transitions
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:771:- A transition from a final state is always forbidden, even with wildcards
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:773:Wildcards are optional. When a machine omits wildcards, only explicitly declared transitions are valid. Engines must not synthesize wildcard transitions; if cancellation from a particular state is desired, it must be declared explicitly (as the default `rhei` machine does).
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:777:There are two valid ways to declare callbacks on transitions:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:779:**1. Platform-prefixed inline identifiers.** The `on_leave`/`on_enter` value includes a platform prefix (`cli:`, `js:`, `py:`, `java:`) followed by the implementation reference. No separate `callbacks:` mapping is needed. Use this when the machine targets a single platform or when each transition has a single implementation.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:782:transitions:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:785:    on_leave: cli:validate_preconditions    # Bash function
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:786:    on_enter: js:startWork                  # JavaScript function
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:789:**2. Logical names with a `callbacks:` mapping.** The `on_leave`/`on_enter` values use platform-agnostic logical names. A top-level `callbacks:` section maps each logical name to platform-specific implementations. Use this when the same machine must work across multiple platforms.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:792:transitions:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:795:    on_leave: prepare_activation   # Logical name, resolved via callbacks:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:797:callbacks:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:806:Both models are valid. They must not be mixed within a single transition (a callback value is either prefixed or logical, not both). When both a prefix and a `callbacks:` mapping exist for the same name, the prefix takes precedence.
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:810:Platform-specific callback mappings allow the same logical callback name to resolve to different implementations:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:813:callbacks:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:815:    <callback-name>: <implementation-path>
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:828:  on_enter_failure:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:829:    - <action>              # Actions to take when on_enter callback fails
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:830:  on_leave_rejection:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:831:    - <action>              # Actions to take when on_leave callback rejects
