docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1615:# Error Handling Lifecycle:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1616:# 1. If on_leave callback rejects (success=false): task stays in current state, no further action
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1617:# 2. If on_leave callback redirects (success=true, nextState): redirect is validated, then on_enter runs
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1618:# 3. If on_enter callback fails: rollback to original state FIRST, then error_handling policy applies
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1619:# 4. Error handling policy determines what happens AFTER rollback (e.g., transition to 'retrying')
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1622:  # What happens when on_enter callback fails (after rollback to original state)
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1623:  on_enter_failure:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1626:    - transition_to: retrying  # This is a NEW transition from the original state
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1628:  # What happens when on_leave callback rejects (success=false)
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1629:  on_leave_rejection:
docs/specs/rhei-transitions.spec.md:1632:    - emit_event: transition_rejected
