docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:125:- `state.agent` on a `final: true` state is a validation error (terminal states have no work to execute).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:126:- `state.agent` on a `gating: true` state is a validation warning (gating states are human-only; the agent will never be invoked by `rhei run`).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:131:- `state.program` on a `final: true` state is a validation error (terminal states have no work to execute).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:132:- `state.program` on a `gating: true` state is a validation error (gating states require human action; programs execute autonomously).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:134:- `state.inputs` / `state.outputs`, when present, must be arrays of unique artifact definitions keyed by `name`.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:135:- Artifact `path` values must be relative to the plan's execution root (the plan-file directory for a single-file plan, or the workspace root for a directory workspace; see [main spec — State Artifact Contracts](../rhei.spec.md#10-state-artifact-contracts)) and must not escape that root after template expansion.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:136:- `artifact.optional`, when present, must be a boolean. Only valid on `inputs` entries; declaring `optional: true` on an `outputs` entry is a validation error (required outputs are always enforced).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:142:- `state.mcp_servers` and `state.skills` on a `gating: true` state are a validation error (gating states are human-only; the agent will never be invoked).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:145:- `state.poll`, when present, must be an object with `interval` (a valid duration string, e.g. `30s`, `5m`, `1h`) and `max_attempts` (an integer ≥ `1`).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:146:- `state.poll` on a `final: true` state is a validation error (terminal states have no work to execute).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:147:- `state.poll` on a `gating: true` state is a validation error (gating states require human action; polling executes autonomously).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:148:- `state.poll` combined with `state.visits` is a validation error. `poll.max_attempts` replaces the `visits` cap for the poll state and populates the same `stateVisits` counter.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:149:- A state that declares `poll` must have at least one self-loop transition (`from: <state>, to: <state>`); without it the "retry" branch is unreachable.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:151:Counted-loop counters are task-instance data, not state-definition data. The state machine declares the cap with `visits`; runtimes persist the current per-task counts in task metadata and mirror the active visit in markdown by appending `-<n>` to `**State:**` for visits greater than `1`.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:153:When a state declares `all_targets` and `visits`, the engine runs the state
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:159:A state marked with a `poll:` block is a *time-triggered* state: on each attempt
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:160:the state's `agent` or `program` runs once, the engine evaluates transitions,
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:161:and a self-loop transition is interpreted as "not done yet, come back in
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:164:`--parallel` slot during the wait.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:173:    poll:
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:180:| `interval` | duration string | Yes | Minimum wall-clock wait between attempts (e.g., `30s`, `5m`, `1h`). The `--parallel` slot is released during the wait. |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:185:- **Attempt counter.** `poll.max_attempts` replaces the `visits` cap for the state. The same `metadata.tasks.<id>.stateVisits.<state-name>` counter records attempts; the counter starts at `1` on first entry and increments on every self-loop re-entry, identical to the `visits` accounting in [Transitions Specification — Counted Loops](rhei-transitions.spec.md#counted-loops).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:186:- **Retry signal.** Any self-loop transition (`from: X, to: X`) selected by the normal transition-matching rules is interpreted as "not done yet." The engine persists `metadata.tasks.<id>.pollNextAttemptAt.<state-name> = now() + interval`, releases the slot, and stops working this task for this pass. On later passes the task is excluded from the ready set until `pollNextAttemptAt` has elapsed.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:187:- **Exit.** Any non-self-loop transition exits the state normally and clears both `pollNextAttemptAt.<state-name>` and `stateVisits.<state-name>` for that state.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:188:- **Exhaustion.** When `stateVisits.<state-name> >= poll.max_attempts`, the engine will *not* execute a self-loop transition even if one matches. Instead it re-evaluates transitions and picks the first matching non-self-loop. The recommended pattern is an explicit exhaustion transition:
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:192:    condition: pollAttempts >= pollMaxAttempts
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:194:  If no non-self-loop matches after exhaustion, the task remains in its current state and `rhei run` aborts the task with a clear error (same behavior as "no matching transition found").
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:196:### Variables for transition conditions
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:199:and `visits`:
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:201:- `pollAttempts` — alias for `visitCount` in a poll state (the current attempt index, `1`-based).
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:202:- `pollMaxAttempts` — alias for `poll.max_attempts`.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:204:Both names are available only on transitions whose `from` state declares
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:205:`poll:`. Outside a poll state they are undefined.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:209:- **`agent` / `program`.** `poll` works for both. The attempt is one subprocess invocation whose exit code / outputs drive transition matching as usual.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:210:- **`all_targets` / `all_models`.** Fanout composes: each per-target or per-model execution tracks its own `stateVisits.<state-name>` entry (same scoping as `visits`). Slot release applies per fanout invocation.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:211:- **`concurrent`.** Independent: a `concurrent: true` poll state may have multiple tasks in flight simultaneously, each with its own `pollNextAttemptAt`.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:212:- **`agent_timeout` / `program_timeout`.** Bound one attempt's duration; they do not bound the total polling wall-clock time. Combine with `max_attempts` to bound the total.
