docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:346:The `instructions` and `personality` fields support template variable substitution. Variables use the same `{variable}` syntax as artifact path templates. `rhei next` resolves all template variables before printing output, so agents receive fully expanded prompts with no manual variable resolution required.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:354:| `{state}` | state machine | Canonical unsuffixed state name | `review` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:355:| `{visit_count}` | runtime counter | Current visit number for counted-loop states | `2` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:356:| `{visits}` | state definition | Configured loop budget for the state | `3` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:360:| `{model.provider}` | model selector | Resolved provider id for the current model profile | `anthropic` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:361:| `{model.name}` | model selector | Resolved provider model name for the current model profile | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:366:| `{input.<name>.path}` | artifact contract | Resolved path of a declared input artifact | `runtime/results/3.md` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:367:| `{input.<name>.exists}` | artifact contract | Whether the input artifact file exists on disk at resolution time | `true`, `false` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:368:| `{output.<name>.path}` | artifact contract | Resolved path of a declared output artifact | `runtime/findings/3.md` |
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:375:- **Resolve at output time, not load time.** Template variables are expanded by `rhei next` when printing instructions to an agent. The state machine YAML remains portable — the same `states.yaml` works across different plans.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:377:- **Pure substitution, no expressions.** Templates produce text, not decisions. Conditional logic belongs in transition `condition` fields, not in instructions. The resolved text tells the agent "you are on pass 2 of 3" — the agent reads that to decide what to do.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:378:- **Artifact references create a single source of truth.** Using `{input.<name>.path}` or `{output.<name>.path}` instead of repeating raw paths means the artifact contract defines the path once. If the path changes, instructions stay correct automatically.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:379:- **`{visit_count}` and `{visits}` are only meaningful for counted-loop states.** For states without a `visits` declaration, `{visits}` is left unresolved and `{visit_count}` resolves to `1`.
docs/specs/rhei-states.spec.md:381:- **Conditional blocks suppress whole paragraphs.** Use `{if input.<name>.exists}`, `{if mcp.<name>.available}`, or `{if skill.<id>.available}` … `{endif}` to include a block of text only when the referenced artifact, server, or skill is present. Use `{else}` between the opening tag and `{endif}` for an alternative block. The entire block — including surrounding blank lines — is removed from the output when the condition is false. Conditional blocks may not be nested in v1.
