docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:5:For the plan grammar see the [Plan Language Specification](../rhei.spec.md). For the state machine see the [States Specification](rhei-states.spec.md). For the TUI that runs alongside `rhei run`, see [Run TUI](rhei-run-tui.spec.md) — `rhei viz` is a distinct command aimed at static plan inspection, not live parallel execution.
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:11:3. **Be self-contained.** The rendered artifact is a single HTML file. No network access, no CDN dependencies, no build step at view time.
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:16:- **Not a replacement for `rhei run`'s TUI.** `rhei viz` does not follow live execution; it snapshots the plan as it is on disk. For live parallel-run visualization, use `rhei run --tui` (see [Run TUI](rhei-run-tui.spec.md)).
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:104:| All top-level tasks are terminal-success (`completed`) | `completed` |
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:105:| All top-level tasks are terminal (`completed`, `cancelled`, `archived`) and at least one is not `completed` | `archived` |
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:109:Derivation is done from the active state machine's terminal-state declarations — a plan using a custom state machine still derives correctly as long as the machine declares its terminal states.
docs/specs/rhei-viz.spec.md:128:- On change: reparses the affected plan and pushes a `PlanUpdated` event over a long-poll or `EventSource` channel.
