docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:3:Reset every task in a plan to its resolved profile's `initial` state and remove runtime output. This is the inverse of a forward run: it restores the plan to a clean, pre-execution state so the same plan can be re-executed from scratch.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:15:1. Load the state machine and plan. Validate the plan (reset refuses to operate on an invalid plan).
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:18:   - Resolve the task's profile through `node_policy`.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:19:   - Rewrite the task's `**State:**` line to the profile's `initial` state.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:22:   - Clear any counted-visit suffix; `stateVisits` entries for the task in frontmatter `metadata.tasks.<id>.stateVisits` are deleted.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:23:4. For a directory workspace, delete the `runtime/` directory at the workspace root if it exists. For a single-file plan, delete the `runtime/` directory next to the plan file if it exists. This removes result files, findings, logs, and journaled transition records.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:30:- Alter the state machine or template source of the plan.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:36:Because reset operates under a file lock, it is safe against concurrent `rhei next` / `rhei transition` / `rhei complete` calls: those calls either run before the reset acquires the lock or after it releases.
docs/specs/rhei-reset.spec.md:59:`rhei reset` inverts the forward commands (`next`, `transition`, `complete`, `run`): it returns every task to its profile's `initial` state and removes the `runtime/` directory.
