     1	# Rhei Transitions Specification
     2	
     3	Formal specification for state transitions with associated function callbacks.
     4	
     5	State transitions will be defined declaratively in YAML and executed through platform-specific mechanisms:
     6	- **CLI**: Bash function calls
     7	- **JavaScript**: Native callbacks via NAPI to javascript functions.
     8	- **Python**: Native callbacks via PyO3 bindings to python functions
     9	- **Java**: Calls to Java functions with JNI
    10	
    11	### Goals
    12	
    13	1. Define state transition rules in YAML that specify valid `from -> to` state changes
    14	2. Associate each transition with a function identifier that gets invoked:
    15	  1. entering the state has one call
    16	  2. leaving the state has another call that returns what is the next state
    17	3. Provide a consistent API across CLI, JavaScript, Python, and Java
    18	
    19	### Requirements
    20	- State transitions must be explicitly declared - unlisted transitions are forbidden
    21	- Transitions trigger callbacks/functions that receive context about the task
    22	- Callbacks can reject transitions by returning an error (for conditional logic)
    23	- Failed transitions should be reportable and recoverable
    24	- Registered callbacks must be verified as callable before execution begins (callback existence validation)
    25	- Callbacks (`on_leave`, `on_enter`) are optional per transition - omitted callbacks are treated as implicit success
    26	
    27	---
    28	
    29	## TransitionContext Data Structure
    30	
    31	The `TransitionContext` is the core data structure passed to all transition callbacks. It provides complete context about the rhei, the transitioning task, and the execution environment.
    32	
    33	```typescript
    34	type TaskId = string | number;
    35	
    36	/**
    37	 * Metadata associated with a task.
    38	 *
    39	 * Note: `state` and `dependsOn` (prior) are always present as implicit fields
    40	 * and don't need to be declared in the metadata section.
    41	 *
    42	 * Custom metadata (like retryCount, priority, etc.) is stored in the YAML
    43	 * metadata section of the rhei file and is available here.
    44	 */
    45	interface TaskMetadata {
    46	  /** Current state of the task - always present, managed by Rhei */
    47	  state: string;
    48	  /** Task dependencies (prior tasks) - always present */
    49	  dependsOn: Array<string | number>;
    50	  /** Custom metadata fields - any additional key-value pairs from YAML */
    51	  [key: string]: any;
    52	}
    53	
    54	/** A task being transitioned within the rhei */
    55	interface TaskNode {
    56	  id: TaskId;
    57	  title: string;
    58	  kind: string;
    59	  metadata: TaskMetadata;
    60	  content: string;
    61	  children: TaskNode[];
    62	}
    63	
    64	/** A required file artifact declared by the active state */
    65	interface StateArtifact {
    66	  name: string;
    67	  path: string;
    68	  format?: string;
    69	  description?: string;
    70	  exists: boolean;
    71	}
    72	
    73	/** Active state definition after template resolution */
    74	interface StateDefinition {
    75	  name: string;
    76	  description: string;
    77	  instructions?: string;
    78	  personality?: string;
    79	  final?: boolean;
    80	  gating?: boolean;
    81	  visits?: number;
    82	  inputs?: StateArtifact[];
    83	  outputs?: StateArtifact[];
    84	}
    85	
    86	/** The rhei containing the transitioning task */
    87	interface Rhei {
    88	  title: string;
    89	  /** Path to the plan file */
    90	  path: string;
    91	  tasks: TaskNode[];
    92	}
    93	
    94	/** Details about the state transition being performed */
    95	interface TransitionInfo {
    96	  from: string;
    97	  to: string;
    98	  /**
    99	   * How this transition was initiated:
   100	   * - 'user': Explicitly triggered via API (CLI command, programmatic call)
   101	   * - 'callback': Triggered by a callback's nextState override
   102	   * - 'system': Triggered by condition evaluation or timeout
   103	   * - 'engine': Triggered by the Rhei engine during autonomous workflow execution
   104	   */
   105	  triggeredBy: 'user' | 'callback' | 'system' | 'engine';
   106	  timestamp: string;  // ISO 8601 format (e.g., "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z")
   107	}
   108	
   109	/** Execution environment information */
   110	interface Environment {
   111	  /** Runtime platform. Use 'nodejs' for JavaScript/TypeScript environments. */
   112	  platform: 'cli' | 'nodejs' | 'python' | 'java';
   113	  version: string;
   114	  workingDirectory: string;
   115	}
   116	
   117	/**
   118	 * The context object passed to all transition callbacks.
   119	 *
   120	 * This provides complete information about:
   121	 * - The rhei being executed
   122	 * - The specific task transitioning between states
   123	 * - Details about the transition itself
   124	 * - Data accumulated during this transition
   125	 * - The execution environment
   126	 */
   127	interface TransitionContext {
   128	  /** The rhei being executed */
   129	  rhei: Rhei;
   130	
   131	  /** The specific task transitioning */
   132	  task: TaskNode;
   133	
   134	  /** Active state definition for the task, including resolved artifact contracts */
   135	  state: StateDefinition;
   136	
   137	  /** Transition details */
   138	  transition: TransitionInfo;
   139	
   140	  /** Data accumulated during this transition (from on_leave to on_enter) */
   141	  transitionData: Record<string, any>;
   142	
   143	  /** Execution environment */
   144	  environment: Environment;
   145	}
   146	
   147	/**
   148	 * The result returned from transition callbacks.
   149	 *
   150	 * Callbacks return one of three distinct outcomes:
   151	 *
   152	 * 1. **Success**: Transition proceeds to the declared target state.
   153	 *    ```typescript
   154	 *    return { success: true };
   155	 *    return { success: true, data: { ... } };
   156	 *    ```
   157	 *
   158	 * 2. **Redirect**: Transition proceeds, but to a different valid target state.
   159	 *    The redirected transition MUST be declared in the state machine.
   160	 *    ```typescript
   161	 *    return { success: true, nextState: 'other-state' };
   162	 *    ```
   163	 *
   164	 * 3. **Rejection**: Transition is blocked; task remains in current state.
   165	 *    ```typescript
   166	 *    return { success: false, error: 'Reason for rejection' };
   167	 *    ```
   168	 *
   169	 * Note: `success: false` with `nextState` is invalid and will be treated as rejection.
   170	 */
   171	interface TransitionResult {
   172	  /** Whether the callback approves the transition proceeding */
   173	  success: boolean;
   174	  /** Error message explaining why the transition was rejected (only when success=false) */
   175	  error?: string;
   176	  /**
   177	   * Redirect to a different target state (only when success=true).
   178	   * The redirect MUST correspond to a declared transition from the current state.
   179	   */
   180	  nextState?: string;
   181	  /** Data to pass to subsequent callbacks in this transition */
   182	  data?: Record<string, any>;
   183	}
   184	```
   185	
   186	### Usage Example
   187	
   188	```typescript
   189	function findTask(nodes: TaskNode[], id: string | number): TaskNode | undefined {
   190	  for (const node of nodes) {
   191	    if (node.id === id) return node;
   192	    const nested = findTask(node.children, id);
   193	    if (nested) return nested;
   194	  }
   195	  return undefined;
   196	}
   197	
   198	rhei.onLeave('pending', 'processing', async (ctx: TransitionContext): Promise<TransitionResult> => {
   199	  // Check dependencies before allowing transition
   200	  for (const depId of ctx.task.metadata.dependsOn) {
   201	    const depTask = findTask(ctx.rhei.tasks, depId);
   202	    if (depTask && depTask.metadata.state !== 'completed') {
   203	      return { success: false, error: `Dependency ${depId} not completed` };
   204	    }
   205	  }
   206	  return { success: true, data: { validatedAt: ctx.transition.timestamp } };
   207	});
   208	```
   209	
   210	> **More examples:** See [Transition Callback Examples](rhei-callbacks.spec.md) for comprehensive examples across all supported languages (TypeScript, Python, Java, Bash) covering dependency validation, data passing, state redirection, custom metadata access, and environment-aware logic.
