  1548	### Example 7: Error Handling and Recovery
  1549	
  1550	Demonstrating how transitions handle errors and recovery:
  1551	
  1552	**states-with-recovery.yaml:**
  1553	```yaml
  1554	name: resilient-workflow
  1555	version: 1.0
  1556	
  1557	states:
  1558	  ready:
  1559	    description: Task is queued and waiting to start
  1560	  processing:
  1561	    description: Main work phase
  1562	  retrying:
  1563	    description: Automatic retry in progress
  1564	  manual-intervention:
  1565	    description: Human operator needed
  1566	    gating: true
  1567	  completed:
  1568	    description: Task finished successfully
  1569	    final: true
  1570	  abandoned:
  1571	    description: Task permanently abandoned after manual review
  1572	    final: true
  1573	
  1574	transitions:
  1575	  - from: ready
  1576	    to: processing
  1577	    on_enter: start_processing
  1578	    max_retries: 0  # No automatic retry for initial transition
  1579	
  1580	  - from: processing
  1581	    to: completed
  1582	    on_leave: validate_output
  1583	    on_enter: finalize
  1584	
  1585	  - from: processing
  1586	    to: retrying
  1587	    on_leave: log_failure
  1588	    on_enter: schedule_retry
  1589	    retry_delay: 30s
  1590	
  1591	  - from: retrying
  1592	    to: processing
  1593	    on_leave: check_retry_count
  1594	    on_enter: start_processing
  1595	    max_retries: 3
  1596	
  1597	  - from: retrying
  1598	    to: manual-intervention
  1599	    on_leave: escalate
  1600	    on_enter: notify_operators
  1601	    condition: retryCount >= maxRetries
  1602	
  1603	  - from: manual-intervention
  1604	    to: processing
  1605	    on_leave: operator_approved
  1606	    on_enter: start_processing
  1607	
  1608	  - from: manual-intervention
  1609	    to: abandoned
  1610	    on_leave: document_abandonment
  1611	    on_enter: cleanup
  1612	
  1613	# Error handling configuration
  1614	#
  1615	# Error Handling Lifecycle:
  1616	# 1. If on_leave callback rejects (success=false): task stays in current state, no further action
  1617	# 2. If on_leave callback redirects (success=true, nextState): redirect is validated, then on_enter runs
  1618	# 3. If on_enter callback fails: rollback to original state FIRST, then error_handling policy applies
  1619	# 4. Error handling policy determines what happens AFTER rollback (e.g., transition to 'retrying')
  1620	#
  1621	error_handling:
  1622	  # What happens when on_enter callback fails (after rollback to original state)
  1623	  on_enter_failure:
  1624	    - log_error
  1625	    - increment_retry_count
  1626	    - transition_to: retrying  # This is a NEW transition from the original state
  1627	
  1628	  # What happens when on_leave callback rejects (success=false)
  1629	  on_leave_rejection:
  1630	    - log_rejection
  1631	    - remain_in_current_state
  1632	    - emit_event: transition_rejected
  1633	```
